Given your work on **Vibecheck** and **Solaris-Agent**, here's a battle-tested breakdown of the most impactful things you can add to a blue team — organized by layer.

***

## Core Detection Stack

The foundation of any effective blue team is a solid **SIEM + EDR** combo. These work in tandem: EDR (like CrowdStrike Falcon or Wazuh) detects suspicious endpoint activity, while SIEM (Splunk, Elastic Security, or Microsoft Sentinel) correlates logs and raises alerts across the entire environment. Feeding EDR-generated IoCs directly into SIEM correlation rules is one of the highest-leverage improvements you can make. [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/arya-chowkekar-145882252_blueteam-cybersecurity-socanalyst-activity-7354770563053105154-TI2z)

- **Wazuh** – Open-source SIEM with continuous threat detection, great for self-hosted setups [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)
- **Elastic Security** – Combines SIEM, endpoint protection, and threat hunting in one stack [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)
- **Microsoft Sentinel** – Cloud-native SIEM with AI-assisted analytics, ideal if you're in Azure [cybernx](https://www.cybernx.com/blue-team-tools/)
- **CrowdStrike Falcon** – Industry-leading EDR with MITRE ATT&CK mapping built in [hackthebox](https://www.hackthebox.com/blog/soc-analyst-tools-essentials-for-blue-teams)

***

## Network Visibility

Blind spots in network traffic are where attackers live the longest. You need full packet capture and intrusion detection layered together. [tryhackme](https://tryhackme.com/resources/blog/blue-team-best-practices)

- **Security Onion** – All-in-one network monitoring suite (IDS + PCAP + log analysis) [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)
- **Arkime** – Full packet capture and indexing for deep session forensics [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)
- **Suricata / Snort** – Real-time IDS/IPS for detecting network-level attack signatures [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/arya-chowkekar-145882252_blueteam-cybersecurity-socanalyst-activity-7354770563053105154-TI2z)
- **RITA** – Uses ML to detect beaconing and C2 communication patterns that rule-based tools miss [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)
- **Maltrail** – Suspicious traffic detection using known bad IPs/domains [linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/vistasec_blueteam-threathunting-cyberdefense-activity-7394746860034392064-eDOf)

