## Process Improvements (Often Overlooked)

Tools alone won't save you — process is where most teams leak. [hackthebox](https://www.hackthebox.com/blog/soc-analyst-tools-essentials-for-blue-teams)

- Build a **SOAR** playbook layer (using tools like Shuffle or Cortex XSOAR) to automate repetitive response actions
- Establish **detection engineering** as a practice: write, test, and version-control detection rules like code
- Regularly review **incident handling methodologies** — HackTheBox research shows ~30% of SOC analysts rank this as the single most important knowledge domain [hackthebox](https://www.hackthebox.com/blog/soc-analyst-tools-essentials-for-blue-teams)
- Run **tabletop exercises** simulating ransomware or supply chain attacks to stress-test your runbooks [tryhackme](https://tryhackme.com/resources/blog/blue-team-best-practices)

Given that you're building Vibecheck for semantic vulnerability detection, integrating your detections directly into a Wazuh or Elastic pipeline with custom rule feeds would be a natural and powerful combination.